      • saveEvent

        public Event saveEvent(String player,
              String op,
              Event.EventType type,
              String reason,
              int expires)
        Write an Event to storage. This method is used to save an Event to the storage for later use. It is also responsible for firing Mjolnir.preProcess(it.flaten.mjolnir.beans.Event) and Mjolnir.postProcess(it.flaten.mjolnir.beans.Event), and respecting NewEventEvent.isCancelled().
        Specified by:
        saveEvent in interface Storage
        Parameters:
        player - The name of the player this Event belongs to.
        op - The name of the player who created this event.
        type - The Event.EventType of this Event.
        reason - The reason for this Event.
        expires - A UNIX timestamp denoting expiration time.
        Returns:
        The resulting Event.
